                    <comment id="12888794" author="halderen" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2010 14:29:16 +0100"  >The following unit test shows the problem, although as indicated, the issue has broader consequences.&lt;br/&gt;
IssueTest can be placed in jackrabbit-core/src/test/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/core/IssueTest.java and when run will throw the ClassCastException.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12888796" author="halderen" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2010 14:32:42 +0100"  >The attached patch resolves this issue by making sure a path passed to resolvePath can fully be resolved.&lt;br/&gt;
The patch is against the 1.5.7 patch, but can be applied to jackrabbit-trunk or other versions as well.</comment>
                    <comment id="12891167" author="stefan@jira" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2010 15:02:13 +0100"  >i applied the provided patch on trunk which lead to several unit test failures.</comment>
                    <comment id="12891173" author="stefan@jira" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2010 15:05:49 +0100"  >this issue is caused by a bug in o.a.jackrabbit.spi.commons.name.PathFactoryImpl which allows to create illegal paths, such as &amp;quot;/a/../../b&amp;quot;.</comment>
                    <comment id="12891185" author="stefan@jira" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2010 15:23:51 +0100"  >fixed in trunk (svn r966672)</comment>
